Child 53:
Entry: **extraction **
Entry: means the activities performed to extract minerals or natural resources from the ground, including by operating equipment to extract minerals or natural resources from mines and wells, or to extract minerals or natural resources from the waste or residue
Entry:  
Entry: of prior extraction.
Entry:  
Entry: Extraction concludes when activities are performed to convert raw mined or harvested products or raw well effluent to substances that can be readily transported or stored for direct use in processing critical minerals;
Entry:

Entry: - critical
Entry: - minerals sector by foreign entities
Entry: - for purposes
Entry: - of assisting a determination by the
Entry: - Party of the effect of such investments on its national security.
Entry: - When appropriate and consistent with their applicable regulatory frameworks, the Parties may notify each other of such investments.

Child 137:
Entry: - Each Party confirms its intention to discourage, through initiatives it considers appropriate, the importation of goods produced in whole or in part by forced or compulsory labor, including forced or compulsory child labor.
Entry: - In this regard, each Party may consider opportunities to discourage the importation into its territory of goods containing critical minerals extracted or processed in whole or in part by forced or compulsory labor, including forced or compulsory child labor.

Entry: - The Parties recognize the importance
Entry: - of remediating situations of forced labor, and of seeking to ensure that victims of forced labor involved in the production of goods receive appropriate remediation.

Child 205:
Entry: Either
Entry:  
Entry: Party
Entry:  
Entry: may
Entry:  
Entry: terminate
Entry:  
Entry: this
Entry:  
Entry: Agreement
Entry:  
Entry: at
Entry:  
Entry: any
Entry:  
Entry: time
Entry:  
Entry: by
Entry:  
Entry: providing
Entry:  
Entry: written
Entry:  
Entry: notice
Entry:  
Entry: of
Entry:  
Entry: termination to the other Party.
Entry:  
Entry: A Party that intends to terminate this Agreement shall provide at least 90 days’ written notice
Entry:  
Entry: to the
Entry:  
Entry: other Party.
Entry:  
Entry: The termination shall take
Entry:  
Entry: effect four
Entry:  
Entry: months after the date on which a Party has provided
Entry:  
Entry: that written
Entry:  
Entry: notice
Entry:  
Entry: to the
Entry:  
Entry: other Party, or
Entry:  
Entry: on such other date as the Parties may
Entry:  
Entry: decide.
Entry:
